                    "text": "had his mind set on",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " becoming a doctor, and nothing could change his ambition"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Shows strong determination. Often used when plans later change unexpectedly ('I had my mind set on med school until I discovered engineering')."
        },
        {
            "word": "As for me",
            "wordType": "phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "Used to shift the topic of conversation to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "yourself",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " after discussing someone or something "
                },
                {
                    "text": "else",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "أما أنا",
            "synonyms": [
                "Regarding me",
                "Speaking for myself",
                "In my case"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "\"My brother loves spicy food.\" \""
                },
                {
                    "text": "As for me",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": ", I can't handle anything hotter than black pepper.\""
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Smooth transition phrase in conversations. More natural than 'And me...' which sounds incomplete. Often shortened to 'As for...' before nouns ('As for dinner, I'm not hungry')."
        },
        {
            "word": "You mean",
